    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.16-17_0001a" />
               
               <fw type="letterhead"> 
                Skyrim Farm                    <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
                   <lb/>
                Route 7
                   <lb/> 
                Columbia, Mo.  
               </fw>
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Nov. 1st, '61</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Edna:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I just want to say hello to you and assure you that I often think of you. Say hello to old John and to Hugh for me. I suppose I may be out there again next summer, altho' I'm not sure. If I come, of course I'll see you people again.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>With affection,</salute>
                
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="authorial">(see over)</note>
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.34.16-17_0001b"/>
                <fw type="curatorial"><del><unclear>24</unclear></del></fw>
                
                <postscript>
                <opener><hi rend="caps">P. S.</hi></opener>
                
                <p>Did you hear that <del/> the Nebraska Legislature voted unanimously to place a bronze bust of me in the Capitol Building at Lincoln? There will be a bronze bust here at the University too. These things generally happen when one is good and dead!</p>
                <closer>
                <signed>John.</signed>
                </closer>
                </postscript>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">16</fw>
            </div1>
            
            
            
